Now the real root cause is visible:

bundle unpacking failed. Reason: DeadlineExceeded

So this is no longer a CSV conflict problem.
OLM cannot unpack the operator bundle image for odf-dependencies.

This usually happens because of:

image pull issue

registry connectivity

insufficient resources

unpack job stuck

failed bundle unpack pod/job


Check unpack jobs:

oc get jobs,pods -A | grep -i unpack

Then describe the failed unpack job/pod:

oc describe job -n openshift-marketplace <unpack-job-name>

and:

oc logs -n openshift-marketplace <unpack-pod-name>

Also check if marketplace operators are healthy:

oc get pods -n openshift-marketplace

and:

oc get co marketplace olm operator-lifecycle-manager

Very commonly on disconnected or unstable registry environments, the unpack pod cannot pull the bundle image.

Also verify pull manually:

oc adm release info registry.redhat.io/odf4/odf-operator-bundle-rhel9:v4.19.12

If unpack pods are stuck in:

ImagePullBackOff

ErrImagePull

Pending

DeadlineExceeded


then we can fix the exact underlying issue directly.

